r\n to realize.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Vedic method, worshipping the devatas, allows for immor=\r\ntality, through Soma devata.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; &gt; (3) The ones in scriptures wh=\r\no actively pursued the divinization/immortalization of physical body did no=\r\nt succeed. For example, king Trishanku wanted to ascend to the immortal pla=\r\nne in his physical body. His family guru Maharshi Vasishtha refused to help=\r\n\n him. Maharshi Vishwamitra tried to help, but did not succeed!&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;OTOH=\r\n, if one doesn&#39;t perform the yagna correctly, Indra doesn&#39;t allow the ascen=\r\nt of mind, what to say of the body.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; All scriptures, whether it =\r\nis Upanishads or Yoga Vaasishtham, say that you overcome your self-identifi=\r\ncation with the perishable body and identify with that which cannot be dest=\r\nroyed. Then you are liberated.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Divinizing the Physical body itself w=\r\nill remove the sense of self-identification, Ahamkara, in any limited sense=\r\n bound to a Physical body of ones&#39; own possession or of the loved ones. No =\r\none can attain liberation in Physical body, unless one divinizes it - Kriya=\r\n and Jnana are not a substitute to Iccha shakti.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;regards,&lt;BR&gt;Aryama&lt;=\r\nBR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;--- In &lt;A href=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot; target=3D_b=\r\nlank rel=3Dnofollow ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;vedic=\r\n-wisdom@yahoogroups.com&lt;/A&gt;, &quot;silentadmirer_in&quot; &lt;silentadmirer_in@...&gt=\r\n;\n wrote:&lt;BR&gt;&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Namaskar,&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Thanks for taking time to answe=\r\nr, because it opens up new things.&lt;BR&gt;&gt; Change occurs in Physical, Astra=\r\nl and Causal being, with time, all the time. Making it unchangeable, divine=\r\n, only means, to realize that the Ahamkara, caught in here and now of being=\r\n is no \n(Message over 64 KB, truncated)"}}